## Recommended Workflow

### 1. Understand current state first

```
dashboard_state           →  see all apps, their statuses, active overrides
screenshot                →  confirm the visible UI
screenshot { labels: true } → labeled screenshot showing interactive elements
accessibility_snapshot    →  get page structure as text
console_logs              →  check for errors
network_log               →  verify API calls
```

### 2. Set up overrides for local development

```
override_app { action: "set", appName: "@cnic/main", url: "http://localhost:9100/app.js" }
```

After setting an override, the extension panel will auto-sync within ~3 seconds.

### 3. Verify changes are effective

```
dashboard_state  →  confirm overrideUrl shows your localhost URL
screenshot       →  confirm the UI reflects your local code
```

### 4. Browser interactions with Playwright

`playwright_execute` gives you the **full Playwright API** — every action triggers real browser input events via CDP (not synthetic JS events). This means CSS `:hover`, `:focus`, `:active` pseudo-classes all work correctly.

Use `playwright_execute` for: any interaction that needs real input events, auto-waiting, or Playwright locators.
Use `execute` for: quick JS evaluation in page context, reading DOM values, calling page APIs (no real input events).

#### Mouse actions

```
playwright_execute { code: "await page.getByRole('button').click()" }
playwright_execute { code: "await page.getByText('Item').dblclick()" }
playwright_execute { code: "await page.getByText('Item').click({ button: 'right' })" }
playwright_execute { code: "await page.getByText('Item').click({ modifiers: ['Shift'] })" }
playwright_execute { code: "await page.getByText('Item').hover()" }
playwright_execute { code: "await page.getByText('Item').click({ position: { x: 0, y: 0 } })" }
playwright_execute { code: "await page.locator('#source').dragTo(page.locator('#target'))" }
```

#### Hover + verify tooltip/dropdown/menu

```
playwright_execute { code: "await page.hover('.menu-trigger'); await page.waitForSelector('.dropdown-menu', { state: 'visible' })" }
playwright_execute { code: "await page.getByRole('link').hover(); await page.waitForSelector('.tooltip', { state: 'visible' })" }
```

#### Form interactions

