## Safety Rules

1. **Only operate on normal web pages** — never target `chrome://`, `edge://`, or extension pages.
2. **Verify state via runtime checks** — use `dashboard_state` and `execute`, not static HTML assumptions.
3. **Screenshot between major actions** — maintain visual awareness of what the user sees.
4. **Don't assume code changes are live** — always confirm via `dashboard_state` that the override is effective.
5. **Use incremental operations** — prefer targeted `override_app` over broad `reset_all`.
6. **Handle page reloads gracefully** — after `clear_cache_and_reload` or `ensure_fresh_render`, wait before querying state.
7. **Parallel calls are safe** — `dashboard_state` + `screenshot` can run concurrently without timeout issues.
8. **Cookie clearing is origin-scoped** — `clear_cache_and_reload` only removes cookies for the current page's origin. Other sites' cookies are never affected, even with `mode: "aggressive"`.
9. **Mock rules persist until disabled** — always call `network_intercept { action: "disable" }` or `reset` when done with mock testing, so real API traffic is not silently intercepted.

## Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Tool timeout | Call `reset` to re-establish CDP + Playwright sessions |
| Override not reflected | Use `ensure_fresh_render` or `clear_cache_and_reload { clear: "cache,service_workers" }` |
| Panel not syncing | Extension detects changes via 3s polling; wait a few seconds or refresh the panel |
| App not mounting after override | Navigate to the app's route first (e.g., `/j/:journalId/my/edit`) then check status |
| `importMapOverrides not available` | Page may not have loaded yet; wait and retry |
| Debugger not paused | Call `debugger { action: "enable" }` first, then set breakpoints and trigger code execution |
| CSS inspect "Element not found" | Verify selector with `execute { code: "document.querySelector('...')" }` first |
| Session limit reached | Sessions auto-evict oldest when max (5) reached; use `session_manager { action: "remove" }` to free slots |
| Stale cached bundle | `clear_cache_and_reload { clear: "cache,service_workers" }` clears cache + service workers without wiping cookies |
| Need to clear cookies too | `clear_cache_and_reload { clear: "cache,cookies" }` clears cache + cookies for current origin only (other sites unaffected) |
| `playwright_execute` connection error | Call `reset` then retry; ensure relay server is running |
| No console/network logs | Logs are captured after CDP connection is established; re-trigger the action |
| Labeled screenshot shows no labels | Page may have no interactive elements; check `accessibility_snapshot` |
| Cookie read fails in `playwright_execute` | Use `Network.getCookies` via CDP session, **not** `Storage.getCookies`. In extension relay mode, `Storage.getCookies` is a root-session command and will fail. Example: `const cdp = await page.context().newCDPSession(page); const { cookies } = await cdp.send('Network.getCookies', { urls: [page.url()] });` |
| All tabs leased by other agents | Use `connect_tab { url: "your-url" }` to attach a new tab, or ask another agent to `release_tab` |
| Tab lease rejected | Another agent holds the lease; use `list_tabs` to see ownership, then pick an AVAILABLE tab or use `connect_tab` |
